You&#39;re on the right track, flatMap should give you a falttened array containing values. After that you just need to use [Array&#39;s reduce][1] to create the object.

Here how you can do it, in kind-of functional way:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const groups = [
      { name: &#39;group1&#39;, values: [&#39;value1&#39;] },
      { name: &#39;group2&#39;, values: [&#39;value2&#39;, &#39;value3&#39;] }
    ];
    let values = groups
      .flatMap(group =&gt; group.values)
      .reduce((acc, values) =&gt; {
        acc[values] = 0;
        return acc;
      }, {});

    console.log(values);

